{"id":927,"date":"2011-07-18T20:03:48","date_gmt":"2011-07-19T00:03:48","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=927"},"modified":"2025-03-03T09:29:51","modified_gmt":"2025-03-03T05:29:51","slug":"yusuf-ihsan-deen-fiqh","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/07\/18\/yusuf-ihsan-deen-fiqh\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Fiqh: Excellence in Islam requires understanding"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: It was said to the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, \u201cWhich people are the most noble?&#8221; The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>The most noble to Allah are the most righteous.<\/strong>\u201d They said, \u201cThat is not what we are asking about.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>The most noble of people was Joseph, the prophet of Allah, son of the prophet of Allah, son of the friend of Allah.<\/strong>\u201d They said, \u201cThat is not what we are asking about.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Are you asking about the Arabs?<\/strong>\u201d They said yes. The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>The best of you in the time of ignorance are the best of you in Islam, if you have understanding<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 3374, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2378<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <b><i>Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0<\/i><\/b>(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u0650\u064a\u0644\u064e \u0644\u0650\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0645\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0643\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0645